This study, carried out in two cities in southern Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil, 
aims to get understand how people with chronic Chagas disease live in order to 
draw possible nursing actions towards a healthier life. The study has a 
descriptive and exploratory character with a qualitative approach. Data were 
collected through semi-sctructured interviews carried out with ten Chagas 
